cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SD, cs.OH

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a problem related to software maintenance and proposes a solution using program transformations. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with the Expression Problem, which is a well-known problem in the context of modular extension in programming languages. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possibility as the paper mentions invertible transformations, which are related to reversible computing and logic. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is a possibility as the paper discusses the problem of choosing a main axis of decomposition in software development and proposes a solution using program transformations. 
- cs.OH (Other Computer Science) is a catch-all category that could apply if the paper does not fit neatly into any of the other categories.
